result.execSummary:
Jonathan L Watts-Braggs was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jonathan L Watts-Braggs was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jonathan L Watts-Braggs not in court.  Paul Leonard Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has been turned over to the State of CALIFORNIA on May 10, 2022
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Jonathan L Watts-Braggs in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Defendant Jonathan L Watts-Braggs in custody.  John Daniel Flynn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jonathan L Watts-Braggs appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of California.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
